interfaces.label: GlobalSearchBatchedResults
description: Response returned from the {@link GlobalSearchPluginStart | global search service}'s `find` API

children.label: results
description: Results for this batch

interfaces.label: GlobalSearchFindOptions
description: Options for the server-side {@link GlobalSearchPluginStart.find | find API}

children.label: preference
description:
A custom preference token associated with a search 'session' that should be used to get consistent scoring
when performing calls to ES. Can also be used as a 'session' token for providers returning data from elsewhere
than an elasticsearch cluster.

If not specified, a random token will be generated and used. The token is stored in the sessionStorage and is guaranteed
to be consistent during a given http 'session'

children.label: aborted$
description:
Optional observable to notify that the associated `find` call should be canceled.
If/when provided and emitting, the result observable will be completed and no further result emission will be performed.

children.label: client
description:
A ES client of type IScopedClusterClient is passed to the `find` call.
When performing calls to ES, the interested provider can utilize this parameter to identify the specific cluster.

interfaces.label: GlobalSearchFindParams
description: Search parameters for the {@link GlobalSearchPluginStart.find | `find` API}

children.label: term
description: The term to search for. Can be undefined if searching by filters.

children.label: types
description: The types of results to search for.

children.label: tags
description: The tag ids to filter search by.

interfaces.label: GlobalSearchProviderFindOptions
description: Options provided to {@link GlobalSearchResultProvider | a result provider}'s `find` method.

children.label: preference
description:
A custom preference token associated with a search 'session' that should be used to get consistent scoring
when performing calls to ES. Can also be used as a 'session' token for providers returning data from elsewhere
than an elasticsearch cluster.

children.label: aborted$
description:
Observable that emits once if and when the `find` call has been aborted, either manually by the consumer,
or when the internal timeout period as been reached.

When a `find` request is effectively aborted, the service will stop emitting any new result to the consumer anyway, but
this can (and should) be used to cancel any pending asynchronous task and complete the result observable from within the provider.

children.label: client
description:
A ES client of type IScopedClusterClient is passed to the `find` call.
When performing calls to ES, the interested provider can utilize this parameter to identify the specific cluster.

children.label: maxResults
description:
The total maximum number of results (including all batches, not per emission) that should be returned by the provider for a given `find` request.
Any result emitted exceeding this quota will be ignored by the service and not emitted to the consumer.

interfaces.label: GlobalSearchProviderResult
description: Representation of a result returned by a {@link GlobalSearchResultProvider | result provider}

children.label: id
description: an id that should be unique for an individual provider's results

children.label: title
description: the title/label of the result

children.label: type
description: the type of result

children.label: icon
description: an optional EUI icon name to associate with the search result

children.label: url
description:
The url associated with this result.
This can be either an absolute url, a path relative to the incoming request's basePath, or a structure specifying if the basePath should be prepended.

children.label: score
description: the score of the result, from 1 (lowest) to 100 (highest)

children.label: meta
description: an optional record of metadata for this result

interfaces.label: GlobalSearchResultProvider
description: GlobalSearch result provider, to be registered using the {@link GlobalSearchPluginSetup | global search API}

children.label: id
description: id of the provider

children.label: find
description:
Method that should return an observable used to emit new results from the provider.

See {@GlobalSearchProviderResult | the result type} for the expected result structure.

children.label: getSearchableTypes
description:
Method that should return all the possible {@link GlobalSearchProviderResult.type | type} of results that
this provider can return.

misc.label: GlobalSearchProviderResultUrl
description: Structured type for the {@link GlobalSearchProviderResult.url | provider result's url property}

misc.label: GlobalSearchResult
description: Representation of a result returned by the {@link GlobalSearchPluginStart.find | `find` API}
